The Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA) said it has approved the sum of N512 million as payment for arrears to pensioners, who have retired from the service of the administration. Director of Federal Capital Territory ((FCT) Area Council Staff Pension Board (ACSPB), Dr. Nanzing Nden, who disclosed this in Abuja yesterday, explained that the amount, which is for 132 retiring and deceased officers of the six area councils and Local Education Authorities (LEAs), also covered accrued rights and death benefits for personnel, who retired or died before the COVID-19 lockdown. Nden added that the approval is not part of the recent N6.1billion paid by the administration to defray liabilities and entitlements to retirees of both the area councils and LEAs within the last four years, in which a total of 1,464 persons benefited from the payments. He revealed that the N512 million was verified and presented to the FCT minister of state, Dr. Ramatu Tijjani Aliyu, who graciously approved the payment, adding that the amount is being processed through the treasury department to the beneficiaries’ Pension Fund Administrators’ account. “At the time I took over, the board had a pension liability of N3.9 billion in unpaid pension and accrued rights benefit. But over a period of time, we’ve been able to pay this liability and improve on the pay-out”. “We have also implemented Group Life Assurance policy for staff under our management”, he added.  